  "informal_statement": "For every triple of real numbers a, b, c: |a - c| <= |a - b| + |b - c|. The metric-space triangle inequality for real distance (absolute difference).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Case split on the sign of each of a-b, b-c, a-c via abs_cases (8 branches total), which replaces each absolute value with its signed unfolding; linarith closes every resulting purely-linear branch uniformly.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem abs_sub_le (a b c : ℝ) : |a - c| ≤ |a - b| + |b - c|",
