  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode a7e193b6), kernel_verified on the first Solve attempt. Uses the same abs_cases-based case-split technique established by abs_add_le/abs_add_three, this time over 3 sign cases (a-b, b-c, a-c, 8 branches) closed by plain linarith rather than nlinarith since every branch is purely linear once the absolute values unfold. Distinct from abs_add_le/abs_add_three (sum form, |a+b|<=|a|+|b|) and reverse_triangle (||a|-|b||<=|a-b|); this is the classic metric-distance triangle inequality. Deliberately picked to continue offsetting this domain's L1_proof_basics coverage gap (2 of 21 packets before this one).",
